Global Distribution:— India , Himachal Pradesh (Districts: Kangra, Kullu, Shimla and Sirmaur) (
Subramani et al. , 2014
) & Uttarakhand (Districts: Chamoli and Pithoragarh (Upper Kumaon Division)) and Nepal (Sudurpashchim Province, Far West Nepal & Karnali Zone , Mid-Western Nepal ). We have excluded Chamba (Himachal Pradesh) as there is only single specimen mentioned from Kilar, Chamba 58761 (BSD) and our examining of that herbarium specimen shows lack of well-preserved flowers to confirm its identity, as it has only single comparatively large differing flower and leaves so it needs confirmation in field.

